# Settings Updates Section

The `UPDATES` array at the top of `settings-content.tsx` is a static changelog shown to users at the bottom of the Settings page.

## When to update it

After any meaningful feature commit (not fixes, lint, or test-only commits), prepend a new entry:

```ts
{ date: "MMM D", note: "Short plain-English description of the change" },
```

## Rules

- Keep notes under ~80 chars, no technical jargon
- Date format: `"Apr 3"` (no year)
- Most recent entry goes first
- Skip: fix commits, lint/test-only commits, config/tooling changes
- Include: new features, UI changes, admin tools, UX improvements
